By Clara Egbogota Lagos   –     The Chief Missioner, Nasrul-Lahil-l-Fatih Society (NASFAT) has urged Nigerians to support the Federal Government’s efforts to take Nigeria out of the woods. Onike made the plea on Friday in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN). He also urged them to exercise patient with the government, while trying to correct the past anomalies and salvage the nation’s economy. “Nigerians should put their trust in God, and have confidence in their leaders. According to him, they mean well for everyone, and there will soon be light at the end of the tunnel in Nigeria. The cleric, explaining the moral lessons of the Eid-el-Kabir, said that it was an act of generosity. “Eid-el-Kabir, being one of the Islamic rituals, is not aimless in purpose, but an avenue to evoke emotions in the hearts of believers.